body: See the below (complete with typo): This implies that pressing the run button will run 'main.dart' (a normal dart project) on a iPhone. However what actually happens is that it launches it as a normal command line app. Consider removing the flutter deployment target UI for normal Dart projects.

comment_data.body:
Thanks Luke!

Did you have any Flutter apps/projects open when this happened?  The device selector should only appear when a Flutter Module is open so if that's not the case, it's a bug.  That said, it may be confusing even on a good day.

We've talked, in general, about a desire to improve our UI around running and debugging and this comment fits right in.  Perhaps something we can kick around when we're all together.

cc @stevemessick @mit-mit @devoncarew
np! I had Flutter apps open in other windows, but not in that one (I have IntelliJ configured to show each project in a new window). Full window screenshot attached
@lukechurch Which version of the flutter plugin did you have installed?
An update wouldn't hurt. `0.1.2` is a wee bit better though I think you'll see this same behavior.

@pq Yup, now updated, thanks. FWIW, I didn't know there was an update available until I went to find the version in preferences. I'm sure the UI was telling me somewhere, but I didn't notice it. In the early days when we're cycling the plugin quickly we might want to make it a bit louder.

I get a pretty "loud" prompt in the lower, left corner whenever there is an update. But I have heard of others that also don't get that.

@alexander-doroshko can you elaborate on how the update prompting works in IJ?

At a minimum you want update checking on in your preferences...

![screen shot 2016-10-20 at 6 53 10 am](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/67586/19562624/dbb0dcea-9691-11e6-8149-fa03da94b936.png)

But besides that, I'd love to know if there's more that can be done.
I don't know why last checked is 'never'
Ok, well, that's not good!  Curious if @alexander-doroshko has ideas...
PS: dude, how can you not be using the darcula theme.  I mean all the kids are into black these days!

> all the kids are into black these days

someone has to test that you do not [hardcode Darcula-specific colors](https://github.com/flutter/flutter-intellij/pull/343/commits/623680a8b801d77e54ac2f6e07dcef3a90a66cea)! :)

No idea why Never checked for updates for Luke. Someone need to browse that piece of code in IntelliJ Community sources.

> someone has to test that you do not hardcode Darcula-specific colors! :)

FYI @devoncarew --- I may have done this but I know you were in there too.

All I can say is, Darcula is awesome!

@lukechurch with the latest plugin we should just show the pulldown for projects with flutter apps in them. OK to close this issue?

> @pq Happy with my aesthetics now? :)

Much! :dancing_men:
